s (Murinae, Muridae) |journal=Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History |volume=21 |pages=1\u2013138 |hdl=2246/906}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Nowak |first1=R.M. |year=1999 |title=Walker's Mammals of the World, Vol. 2 |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press |location=London }}\n*{{cite journal |ref=harv |doi=10.1080/10635150490468701 |pmid=15371245 |jstor=4135423 |title=Phylogeny and Divergence-Date Estimates of Rapid Radiations in Muroid Rodents Based on Multiple Nuclear Genes |journal=Systematic Biology |volume=53 |issue=4 |pages=533\u201353 |year=2004 |last1=Steppan |first1=Scott |last2=Adkins |first2=Ronald |last3=Anderson |first3=Joel }}\n*{{cite journal |ref=harv |doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2005.04.016 |pmid=15975830 |title=Multigene phylogeny of the Old World mice, Murinae, reveals distinct geographic lineages and the declining utility of mitochondrial genes compared to nuclear genes |journal=Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution |volume=37 |issue=2 |pages=370\u201388 |year=2005 |last1=Steppan |first1=Scott J. |last2=Adkins |first2=R.M. |last3=Spinks |first3=P.Q. |last4=Hale |first4=C. }}\n\n{{Murinae}}\n{{Muridae}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q30266}}\n\n[[Category:Muridae|.]]\n[[Category:Old World rats and mice|.]]\n[[Category:Rats of Asia|.]]\n[[Category:Mammal subfamilies]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Subfamily of rodents}}\n{{More footnotes|date=November 2009}}\n{{Automatic Taxobox\n| name = Old World rats and mice\n| fossil_range = Middle [[Miocene]] \u2013 recent\n| image = Mouse white background.jpg\n| image_caption = ''[[House mouse|Mus musculus]]'', the house mouse\n| taxon = Murinae\n| authority = [[Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger|Illiger]], 1811\n| subdivision_ranks = [[Genus|Genera]]\n| subdivision = \n''[[Abditomys]]''<br>\n''[[Abeomelomys]]''<br>\n''[[Aethomys]]''<br>\n''[[Anisomys]]''<br>\n''[[Anonymomys]]''<br>\n\u2020''[[Antemus]]''<br>\n\u2020''[[Anthracomys]]''<br>\n''[[Apodemus]]''<br>\n''[