v |doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2005.04.016 |pmid=15975830 |title=Multigene phylogeny of the Old World mice, Murinae, reveals distinct geographic lineages and the declining utility of mitochondrial genes compared to nuclear genes |journal=Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution |volume=37 |issue=2 |pages=370\u201388 |year=2005 |last1=Steppan |first1=Scott J. |last2=Adkins |first2=R.M. |last3=Spinks |first3=P.Q. |last4=Hale |first4=C. }}\n\n{{Murinae}}\n{{Muridae}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q30266}}\n\n[[Category:Muridae|.]]\n[[Category:Old World rats and mice|.]]\n[[Category:Rats of Asia|.]]\n[[Category:Mammal subfamilies]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger]]\n", "name_user": "Kwo", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murinae"}
